Comment:
5 out of 5 stars.

Jungle Cruise is a fun awesome adventure film that follows Lily (Emily Blunt) and Skipper (Dwayne Johnson) going on a jungle cruise on an amazon river to find a tulip that can be a solution to diseases. While facing against a German general and his military group. And cursed pioneers who are after the same thing.

Great plot. Great action sequences. Adventurous music score. And a great cast ensemble. Dwayne Johnson and Emily Blunt worked great together with there chemistry. The film has plenty of humor and fun moments that makes this film worth watching. Yes, even being based on the ride at Disneyland. The movie does feel like a wild ride with lots of fun action and a adventure story. The film does have a lot of cgi and visual effects which were great. The references to the ride was a lot of fun.

I saw this movie in the cinema and it was amazing. the first scene was already full of action and when they got to the amazon the jaguar scene and the chase scene through the market and the submarine was all so much fun! This movie probably a 11/10

Comment: The River Boat tour at the beginning of the movie brought back memories of the River Boat ride at Six Flags over Texas back in the late 60's. They also had a lot of the same type of props, instead of the hippo it was an alligator that popped up right next to the boat. The SAME joke about the water was a waterfall at Six Flags and the boat went into the waterfall through a small tunnel and then Indians shooting arrows. Next area was rifles and cannon fire with explosions in the water. Wish I could've gone to Disneyland but that time has passed. I'm sure it's still fun, but the era version of Disneyland I want to see has been gone for many years now. By the way the joke about the cross eyed girlfriend seeing someone on the side had me rolling.

Comment: So I've seen this for the second time now and in all honesty... I enjoyed it. I'm a huge fan of DJ's and I really like Emily Blunts acting. Was the movie perfect? No it was not, but it did give me a warm & fuzzy feeling afterwards. I loved the chemistry between the two stars, I mean that was pure magic right there. Definently the heroes of the whole movie in my opinion. The visuals were stunning, could not go wrong with the special effects. The humore and "bad jokes" were... hilarious! I laughed like a little kid, lol. I liked Jesse Plummers character, flamboyant and charming. But the other supporting cast didn't do it for me. Also could not get behind the soundtrack, nothing against Metallica's Nothing Else Matters and other rock sympohnies heard... just thought it didn't suit the movie. But still, it was a nice family movie and I'm a fan. Actually kinda hoping for a sequel as well but not sure it that'll happen, lol...
